-- UBS sells 3 pct of Spain's Acerinox on behalf of Del Pino family
-- 
-- Thu Jul 03, 2014 11:56AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, July 3 (Reuters) - Investment bank UBS said on Thursday it was selling around 3 percent of Spanish steel maker Acerinox to institutional investors via an accelerated bookbuild.

The bank said it was selling the stake on behalf of Casa Grande de Cartagena, a holding company of one of Spain's richest families and founders of construction and airport management company Ferrovial <FER.MC> - the Del Pino family.